<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Our Mexico team stepped up again and made a real impact. This time, they focused their efforts on a local hospital that needed support and didn't hesitate to help. The team prepared and served 350 tamales and hot coffee to patients and their families.</p>

<h2>More than a meal</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">What the team did wasn't just about handing out food. It gave people a break, a moment to breathe, and a reminder that the community around them cares. Acts like this don't fix every problem, but they make the hard moments a little easier to bear. Our team showed what it looks like to lead with heart, stay connected to the community, and put real action behind the idea of helping others.</p>
